"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-gold-zone-peacock-olympics-paris\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"\\\"Gold Zone,\\\" a live whip-around show that features the most exciting Olympic moments across sports as they are happening, will debut on Peacock during the 2024 Paris Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 172, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Scott Hanson, Andrew Siciliano, Matt Iseman and Akbar Gbajabiamila will be hosts of the show, which streams live daily on Peacock from 7 a.m. to 5 p.m.\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 325, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 174, \"end\": 186, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Hanson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scott Hanson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Hanson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scott_Hanson\"}, {\"begin\": 188, \"end\": 204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Siciliano\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrew Siciliano\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Siciliano\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Siciliano\"}, {\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Iseman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matt Iseman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Iseman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Iseman\"}, {\"begin\": 296, \"end\": 303, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999992535027162, \"rank\": 7.458347719149827e-07, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ET, starting on July 27, the first day of medal competition, through Aug. 10.\", \"from\": 326, \"to\": 403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With up to 40 events happening simultaneously during the Paris Olympic Games, Gold Zone will present viewers with the best and most compelling moments happening at any time,\\\"according to NBC Sports PR.\", \"from\": 405, \"to\": 607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 593, \"end\": 603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"score\": 0.887450692825969, \"rank\": 0.1268151727768661, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The daily live show will guide fans through the excitement, triumphs, and emotion of the Games, scanning all the events that day to provide viewers with the most exhilarating moments and key races, routines, and finishes as they unfold live.\\\"\", \"from\": 608, \"to\": 851, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hanson, who has hosted NFL RedZone since its inaugural season 2009, will open each day's coverage on Peacock.\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_RedZone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NFL RedZone\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_RedZone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_RedZone\"}, {\"begin\": 876, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_RedZone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NFL RedZone\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_RedZone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NFL_RedZone\"}, {\"begin\": 954, \"end\": 961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999992535027162, \"rank\": 7.458347719149827e-07, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Siciliano, who hosted the Red Zone Channel on DIRECTV from 2005 to 2022, returns after hosting NBC Sports' Gold Zone coverage during the 2014 Sochi Winter Games and the 2016 Rio Games.\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 1148, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1059, \"end\": 1069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"score\": 0.887450692825969, \"rank\": 0.1268151727768661, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Iseman and Gbajabiamila return after hosting Peacock's Tokyo Olympic morning show, \\\"Tokyo Live,\\\" in 2021.\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1255, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1195, \"end\": 1202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"score\": 0.9999992535027162, \"rank\": 7.458347719149827e-07, \"text\": \"Peacock\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peafowl\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Special guests will join the show throughout the coverage.\", \"from\": 1257, \"to\": 1315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Gold Zone\\\" will also be available on NBCSports.com and the NBC Sports app via \\\"TV Everywhere\\\" for customers with pay-TV subscriptions.\", \"from\": 1317, \"to\": 1452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1355, \"end\": 1368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"NBCSports.com\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}, {\"begin\": 1377, \"end\": 1387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"score\": 0.887450692825969, \"rank\": 0.1268151727768661, \"text\": \"NBC Sports\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCSN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Division ofNBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1464, \"title\": \"http://dbpe